    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nIt now not possible to add extmark on folded line. This is a **very** useful behavior to have for \"jump\"-like plugins ('hop.nvim', 'mini.jump2d', etc.).\r\n\r\n Works on Neovim 0.9.0. It seems to also have been possible on version `NVIM v0.10.0-dev-387+gd31f7648e`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean`\r\n2. Add lines `aaa`, `bbb`, `ccc`.\r\n3. `:2,3fold`\r\n4. `:lua ns_id = vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test')`\r\n5. `:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, ns_id, 1, 0, { virt_text = { { 'X', 'Error' } }, virt_text_pos = 'overlay' })`. Nothing is shown over folded region, but extmark is there (its text is shown if fold is expanded).\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nExtmark text `X` shown at first column of folded line.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-415+g55f6a1cab\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNo (doesn't have this functionality)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nEndeavourOS Linux x86_64 (6.3.4-arch1-1)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nst-0.9\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nst-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nappimage",
