        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> Are you already treating folded lines differently from non-folded lines? If so I suggest using `virt_text_win_col` instead of `overlay`.\r\n\r\nI treat folded lines differently in that it makes sense to only allow placing extmark on first column (`col = 0`). But I don't treat them differently when placing extmarks.\r\n\r\nUsing `virt_text_win_col` is a bit tricky because I currently process per buffer and `virt_text_win_col` needs information about the left most visible column. I mean, it can be done if there is no other option, but it seems that `overlay` should be enough (if the issue will be resolved, that is).\r\n\r\n**Edit**: Plus there are whole new complications with `virt_text_win_col` regarding tabs. Their visible width should be correctly taken into account and that is painful.\r\n\r\n**Edit**: Plus `wrap`/`nowrap`.",
